<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Psychosurgery&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">See also</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Anti-psychiatry" title="Anti-psychiatry">Anti-psychiatry</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bioethics" title="Bioethics">Bioethics</a> / <a href="/wiki/Medical_ethics" title="Medical ethics">Medical ethics</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Frontal_lobe" title="Frontal lobe">Frontal lobe</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Neurosurgery" title="Neurosurgery">Neurosurgery</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Phineas_Gage" title="Phineas Gage">Phineas Gage</a>, who famously suffered an accident in 1848 which destroyed one or both frontal lobes, and who is often incorrectly said to have undergone "the first lobotomy," or (also incorrectly) to have inspired or influenced the development of lobotomy.</li>
</ul>
